# 💰 Personal Finance Tracker (Core Java)

A high-performance command-line application designed to automate personal expense tracking and financial data management. This project focuses on the core foundations of Java, specifically Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and persistent data storage.

## 🚀 Key Features
* **Data Persistence:** Implemented custom File I/O logic to save and load transactions from local text files.
* **OOP Architecture:** Utilized Encapsulation and abstraction to ensure a clean, maintainable codebase.
* **Dynamic Management:** Uses the Java Collections Framework (ArrayList) for efficient in-memory data handling.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
* **Language:** Java 17/21
* **Concepts:** File I/O (java.io), Collections API, Exception Handling.

## 📈 Learning Outcomes
This project demonstrates my ability to build standalone Java applications that handle real-world data constraints, ensuring information is preserved across user sessions without the need for a heavy database.
